||Customer Campaign Specification Instance Record|##|||The overall record for a customer campaign design|IO|IO|||IO|IO|IO|O
|||Customer Campaign Type|||The type or category of customer campaign (e.g. cross-sell, up-sell, retention)|IO|IO||||IO|IO|O
|||Customer Campaign Description|||A description of the campaign that clarifies the intended context/use of the campaign, the mechanisms employed and the intended/anticipated response/impact|IO|IO||||IO|IO|O
|||Customer Campaign Metrics|##||Metrics that are defined to assess the target and actual impact of the campaign|IO|IO||||IO|IO|O
||||Customer Campaign Metric Definition||A description of the metric, defining how it is to be measured in deployment|IO|IO||||IO|IO|O
||||Customer Campaign Metric Goal||A description of the target performance for the metric that can be defined for different usage scenarios as appropriate|IO|IO||||IO|IO|O
|||Customer Campaign Specification|##||The precise make-up of the campaign. Note that all customer campaign specifications are subject to versioning as the campaign is refined over time.|O|IO||||O|O|O
||||Customer Campaign Product/Service Usage|##|Details how the campaign aligns with selected products and services, including pricing considerations|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Product/Service Type|The type or category of product or service included in the campaign (e.g. current account)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Product/Service Campaign Engagement Description|A description of how the product or service is adapted in the context of the campaign (e.g. discounted pricing/preferential rates, waived service fees, gifts or incentives)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Product/Service Campaign Transfer Pricing Arrangement|Describes how any discounted costs are to be accounted for by the product fulfillment function (e.g. borne by fulfillment business unit, compensated by campaign budget)|O|IO||||O|O|O
||||Customer Campaign Execution Guidelines|##|Guidelines for the execution of the campaign|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Eligibility |Defines the eligibility criteria that are to be applied to select suitable candidates for the customer campaign. (Note candidate lists are developed by Campaign Execution)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Qualifications|Defines any qualifications or credentials required of the bank unit or employees to execute the campaign (e.g. product certified, sign-off authority level)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Interaction Guide|Provides the structured narrative and any pricing/negotiating frameworks that are used in the execution of the campaign|O|IO||||O|O|O
||||Customer Campaign Consumables|##|Design specification of any consumables that are to be used in the execution of the campaign (e.g. brochures)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Consumable Type|The type of consumable item associated with the campaign (e.g. gift, brochure)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||||Customer Campaign Consumable Description|The specification of the consumable item in whatever form appropriate. Note sourcing/procurement of the item is handled by execution)|O|IO||||O|O|O
|||Customer Campaign Performance Record |##||Maintains a record of the use and impact of customer campaign versions over the life of the campaign|IO|IO|||IO|IO|IO|O
